commit.message:
m68hc11.h (INCOMING_RETURN_ADDR_RTX): Remove so that we use setjmp/longjmp exceptions.

	* config/m68hc11/m68hc11.h(INCOMING_RETURN_ADDR_RTX): Remove so
	that we use setjmp/longjmp exceptions.

From-SVN: r45901

files.patch:
@@ -1,3 +1,8 @@
+2001-09-30  Stephane Carrez  <Stephane.Carrez@worldnet.fr>
+
+	* config/m68hc11/m68hc11.h(INCOMING_RETURN_ADDR_RTX): Remove so
+	that we use setjmp/longjmp exceptions.
+
 2001-09-30  Neil Booth  <neil@daikokuya.demon.co.uk>
 
 	* cpphash.h (POOL_ALIGN, POOL_FRONT, POOL_LIMIT, POOL_BASE,

@@ -881,16 +881,6 @@ extern enum reg_class m68hc11_tmp_regs_class;
 
 #define FIRST_PARM_OFFSET(FNDECL)	2
 
-/* A C expression whose value is RTL representing the location of the
-   incoming return address at the beginning of any function, before the
-   prologue.  This RTL is either a REG, indicating that the return
-   value is saved in REG, or a MEM representing a location in
-   the stack.
-  
-   Before the prologue, RA is at 0(sp). */
-#define INCOMING_RETURN_ADDR_RTX \
-    gen_rtx_MEM (VOIDmode, gen_rtx_REG (VOIDmode, STACK_POINTER_REGNUM))
-
 /* After the prologue, RA is at 0(AP) in the current frame.  */
 #define RETURN_ADDR_RTX(COUNT, FRAME)					\
   ((COUNT) == 0								\
